um = -5000000", "output": "-5000000"}, {"input": "num = -56789", "output": "-98765"}, {"input": "num = -1000000000000001", "output": "-1100000000000000"}], "query": "You are an expert Python programmer. You will be given a question (problem specification) and will generate a correct Python program that matches the specification and passes all tests.\n\n### Question:\nYou are given an integer num. Rearrange the digits of num such that its value is minimized and it does not contain any leading zeros.\nReturn the rearranged number with minimal value.\nNote that the sign of the number does not change after rearranging the digits.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: num = 310\nOutput: 103\nExplanation: The possible arrangements for the digits of 310 are 013, 031, 103, 130, 301, 310. \nThe arrangement with the smallest value that does not contain any leading zeros is 103.\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: num = -7605\nOutput: -7650\nExplanation: Some possible arrangements for the digits of -7605 are -7650, -6705, -5076, -0567.\nThe arrangement with the smallest value that does not contain any leading zeros is -7650.\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n-1015 <= num <= 1015\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def smallestNumber(self, num: int) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def smallestNumber(self, num: int) -> int:\n        if num == 0:\n            return 0\n        \n        # Convert the number to a string and remove the sign\n        num_str = str(abs(num))\n        \n        # Sort the digits\n        sorted_digits = sorted(num_str)\n        \n        if num > 0:\n            # Find the first non-zero digit and swap it with the first digit\n            for i, digit in enumerate(sorted_digits):\n                if digit != '0':\n                    # Swap to avoid leading zero\n                    sorted_digits[0], sorted_digits[i] = sorted_digits[i], sorted_digits[0]\n                    break\n            \n            # Join the sorted digits and convert back to integer\n            return int(''.join(sorted_digits))\n        else:\n            # For negative numbers, just reverse the sorted digits to get the smallest value\n            return -int(''.join(sorted_digits[::-1]))\n```\n\nThis code handles both positive and negative numbers by first converting the number to a string, sorting the digits, and then rearranging them to form the smallest possible number without leading zeros. For negative numbers, it simply reverses the sorted digits to achieve the smallest value.", "estimated_date": 1644105600000}